Aviva May Sell RAC, Keep Pension Liabilities, Telegraph Reports

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-04-27T05:17:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/aviva-may-sell-rac-keep-pension-liabilities-telegraph-reports.html
Aviva Plc (AV/)  may sell its RAC roadside
recovery service for about 900 million pounds ($1.5 billion)
after four private equity groups made it through to the second
round of bidding, the  Daily Telegraph  reported, without saying
where it obtained the information.  Aviva may retain the RAC pension liability; the buy-out
firms still bidding are Clayton, Dublier & Rice LLC,  Carlyle
Group ,  BC Partners  and Bain Capital LLC, the newspaper said.    Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
